summary: The red line in my career is that I work on the development and well-being of people. I started my career as a trainer and coach, I made a transition to business at management and entrepreneurial level. By combining the motivations and bottlenecks of employees and deepening the "why" of the employer, I bring people and organization together. In order to maintain a match, I'm working on the personal and professional development of both the staff and the management. Finding and maintaining this match is my driving force. A growing organization with happy or satisfied employees is my goal.
